			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I got invited with a guild group to go to MPG the other day. It was the first time I've ever been there, so it was exciting of course. We started near the blind PH and pulled from there for a while. Not too bad, and I was able to keep the pace up, since everything is spread out. Then someone wanted to move to 6-way... I must of died 6 times in an hour trying to pull around there. I just couldn't get the timing or something right. It probably would've helped if I had more FT (on 2 atm <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />  ) and waited long enough to get mana for a fade after the deaths, but I just felt like I was doing something wrong. Is 65 really too low to be pulling in there? I thought it was, since everything was red, but my group kept trying to reassure me that I was doing fine... I'd like to believe that, but I'm not <i>that</i> naive. </span></td>
