				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A little help on MPG<a name="72596"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 05 2:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First thing is, yes your too low for MPG, i didnt start going there till 68. Next problem is i dont think your pacify works. Ive not played a bard there so i cant really say for sure, i do know that my rangers lvl 68 paci doesnt on most because of their lvls. Most bards rely on fade to pull. Now being your 65 IF you can get a group even tho your low if you can fade successfully you may be able to single. However you have to get used to MPG. Agro ranges there are larger then alot of zones. The timing on fade is a biggie in MPG. 
<br />

<br />
Regarding your FT, you know you can get tribute for FT 5 at your lvl bringing you to 7. I only have FT 4 on my bard from tribute atm but thats only because im lvl 59, once i hit 60 i can get the 5th. 
<br />

<br />
IMO i think you should start in WoS and pull there and get used to pulling singles. Once you hit 67 you could start LFG in MPG. 
<br />

<br />
I cant really get into more detail because i pull there with my ranger and unfortunetly im limited to what camps i can pull because of the lvls on the mobs. Im a ways off from bringing my bard there. 
<br />

<br />
My best advise... Get more FT, turn in some items for tribute and get the tribute FT 5 then increase your mana pool because you need it for all the fading your gonna be doing while pulling. </span></td>
