			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A little help on MPG<a name="72601"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 05 3:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can do it, you're a bard. You just need some time to learn your way around. Pacify doesn't work in MPG, even the new OoW one, so don't sweat it. Without the 67 mezz and not enough mana to fade much, life is rough, but you can still easily hit two of the three nearby nameds. This is the poor man's guide to pulling 6way, no mezz and no fading.
<br />

<br />
BTW, always have PoV up when tagging. Being snared on the pull is the pits. I tend to pull with dispell and then slow because many of the mobs have spell or melee mitagation buffs. But you may choose to pull with HoS and slow.
<br />

<br />
The first is the corner directly south of camp. There are two see-invis mobs there. One is the static PH and the other a roamer. From camp go to the west corner and wait for the roamer to come to you. When you can see it, tag. Then the named/ph will be a single.
<br />

<br />
The second named is off the SW 6way exit. Directly north of  your camp there is a roaming discordling. The discordlings only assist each other and no other mob will assist them. So just tag it. No worries. In the plaza to your left there is the lighting warrior that guards the exit and a roamer. If the roamer is nearby get it first. Otherwise it will assist. It will also be in your way coming back to camp, so you want it early. Go down that SW path, a single huval at the end. Turning left there is a dragorn hiding behind a post. He snares. Make sure you have PoV up. Try to pull by getting close enough to start casting and then pullng out of his cast range before it hits. He's a fast sob and sees invis so if he does snare you, you're toast. I can usually get a mezz on him, but you don't get that till 67. The named is the center mob in the room west of there. He and the PH are discordlings, so tag and he's single.
<br />

<br />
The other mobs in the plaza are all easy single tags if you are patient and let them path around. Watch out for the roaming Aneuk. He gates. His spawn is somewhere far far north and he will bring a dozen or so mobs back with him. So stop gating or camp out. 
<br />

<br />
The third named/ph is at the end of the NE exit on a little platform. This requires a split, so you may have to skip him till later. He can be hard to target, but you don't want to tag him anyway because the mobs on both sides will assist. I usually mezz the one on the right and he comes single. You could try snaring instead, but then you'll have to burn a fade in either case. The roaming discordling there won't assist. You may just want to grab him as an easy single pull.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
