			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A little help on MPG<a name="72998"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 8 05 5:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Your post isn't that different from my post five above it except that's its numbered and you are doing them in a different order. But then again, judging from the three replies right below it, doesn't look like many people read it before saying that MPG is too hard at 65. 
<br />

<br />
It's not really. TF/BH is pullable by anyone. Tanks usually pull. No CC required. That means it's always camped. So you can't simply &quot;insist&quot; on it. Six way is the next easiest. Only one split and that's if you're going to do all 3 named. Most groups settle for two anyway. 
<br />

<br />
Another easy pull area is the road to Arcania. The mobs are all wanderers. There are distinct non-overlapping borders that groups of them roam in. Just stand there and wait and tag when one is single. Obviously, real pullers don't just wait, but this is a camp that can be done with no pullers or CC. Ditto for the road to Power, but its a bit harder to get to. The advantage of these two is, they are hardly ever camped. So even with thirty peeps in the zone, you can find a spot. The disadvantages are the difficulty getting in replacements past the see invis on the way and corpse runs if something goes wrong.
<br />
</span></td>
